-- Serena Williams Wins Fourth Wimbledon Title, Defeating Zvonareva 6-3, 6-2
-- Rob Gloster
-- 2010-07-03T14:22:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-03/serena-williams-wins-fourth-wimbledon-title-defeating-zvonareva-6-3-6-2.html

          
          
             Serena Williams won her fourth
Wimbledon title, defeating Vera Zvonareva 6-3, 6-2 today on
Centre Court for her 13th Grand Slam championship.  
 Williams, 28, an American who has won back-to-back
Wimbledon titles, had seven aces to bring her total for the two-
week tournament to a record 87. Zvonareva, 25, a Russian who was
seeded 21st, was in her first Wimbledon final.  
          
          


  


        